I was so nervous about sharing this. I’m laughing in this video, but PMDD is not a joke. This is PMS on steroids! It starts right after ovulation and stops when your period starts( Luteal Phase). For months, possibly years, I’ve been suffering from it and had no idea what I was dealing with, from depression to anxiety, the panic attacks girlllllllll. It was three much! I haven’t been as consistent on socials as I would like, which was partly why. I’m grateful to have noticed a pattern, and I’m on the path to correcting it( if possible). Because you guys don’t know how much I beat myself up about this. Unfortunatly, from my research, there is still so much unknown about this condition. Not enough research goes into women’s health which is another conversation in itself! I also failed to mention that I did not only google; I did speak to doctors to confirm that this was what I was experiencing. It is usually self-diagnosable, but PLEASE talk to a doctor if you feel this is what you are experiencing. I’m here to tell you that you might not be sad, babe; you might be hormonal. You are that girl, and do not let those thoughts deceive you. I’m learning more, and I will share and bring you guys on this journey with me. If you know someone suffering from this, give them a big hug because I promise you this can be frightening. And if you are suffering from it, girl, I see you, I love you, and it will be okay! We will figure it out together.

In the meantime, girl, I  GOT MY PERIOD. I GOT MY PERIODDDDD! The baddie is back. The Ginga is fully activated!

#womenshealth #PMDD #PMS #Periods #baddie #yougotthis

Sis, I visited Bloomingdale’s, Nordstrom, Lane Bryant, and Soma to get professionally sized and  in search of the perfect bra, but girl I fell flat. None of the bras I tried on fit comfortably. Some were marginally better than others, but I felt like buying any of them would mean settling for discomfort and needing a replacement within six months. That’s not ideal for me. However, the silver lining was what I learned getting professionally fitted. One key takeaway is that your bra size can change depending on the type, such as full coverage or medium coverage. That was an eye-opener for me. This journey to find the perfect bra is proving to be lengthy. The inconsistency in sizing across different brands doesn’t help either. It’s  disappoint how challenging it is to determine the right bra size and to actually find one in stores. A heartfelt thanks to all the wonderful ladies who assisted me; they were so kind and warm though this experience. 🧡
